name: MR. NEGATIVE
biography: Emerging from a shadowy background, the man known as Martin Li was forced to undergo a series of experiments that left him with the power of the extradimensional Darkforce.

name: CAPTAIN MARVEL
biography: A bold leader who doesn't sugarcoat, Carol is guided by a strong sense of duty and honor. Carol brings the heroes together as an official team and ensures they're prepared for the challenges ahead.

name: NICK FURY
biography: A veteran S.H.I.E.L.D. operative, Nick Fury Jr. continues the legacy as one of the greatest super spies in the world.

name: PHIL COULSON
biography: Phil Coulson is the heart of S.H.I.E.L.D, as he works tirelessly to protect the innocent from all kinds of super human threats. He has revered Super Heroes since childhood, and always seeks to uphold their positive legacies.

name: ALEX WILDER
biography: Like the other Runaways, Alex Wilder discovers that his parents are Super Villains in an organization known as the The Pride. Unlike his friends, however, he remains loyal to his family. With his incredible intellect, he manipulates the Runaways.

name: ALPHONSO MACKENZIE
biography: Alphonso “Mac” Mackenzie acts as the CIA’s liaison with S.H.I.E.L.D. and often helps out on missions. Due to his disdain over alien technology and overarching powers, he ends up developing a strained relationship with Director Nick Fury.

name: Não encontrado (74)
biography: When Amadeus Cho took on the powers of the Incredible Hulk, he began a struggle for control between the super genius he’s always been and the destructive force he was destined to become.

name: ANT-MAN
biography: When ex-criminal Scott Lang turned to his illicit skills in order to save his daughter’s life, he unexpectedly became the size-shifting, insect-commanding Super Hero known as Ant-Man!

name: ANUBIS
name2: ANPU (EGYPTIAN TRANSLATION; ANUBIS IS THE GREEK TRANSLATION OF HIS NAME)

name: AURAN
biography: As a faithful member of the Attilan Security Force, Auran has used her superhuman hearing abilities to fight crime amongst the Inhumans. With her partner Frank McGee (whom she renamed Nur), she serves the Inhuman Royal Family.

name: AXUM
name2: DANIEL "DANNY" BROUGHTON; LEGALLY CHANGED TO DANIEL AXUM

name: BAKUTO
biography: Hungry for power, Bakuto made his way through the ranks of the Hand by taking charge – and lives. Bakuto is loyal to no one but himself and seeks unchecked world domination. But he will have to get through Daredevil first.

name: BEAUTIFUL DREAMER
biography: Part of the isolated mutant community of Morlocks, Dreamer makes use of her mind-manipulating abilities to support her brethren.

name: BETA RAY BILL
name2: BILL; LEGALLY CHANGED TO BETA RAY BILL

name: BIG WHEEL
name2: AXEL WEELE; LEGALLY CHANGED TO JACKSON WEELE

name: BLACK BOLT
biography: If there was ever a strong, silent type, it’s Black Bolt, king of the Inhumans. Exposed to Terrigen mists before birth, he obtained a perilously loud voice that causes massive damage with even a whisper.

name: BLACK CAT
biography: A traumatic past and sly father push Black Cat into a life of crime, at which she excels thanks to her abilities. Felicia Hardy allies herself with Spider-Man for the common good and often sets aside her criminal activity to pursue a life of heroics.

name: CULL OBSIDIAN
biography: A brutal and brutish follower of Thanos, this massively strong warrior will do what is needed to accomplish his master’s goals.

name: BLACK MARIAH
biography: Mariah Dillard is a criminal gang leader in New York City who uses her charm and cutthroat tactics seamlessly to carve out her corner of the Five Boroughs.

name: BLACK PANTHER
biography: T’Challa is the king of the secretive and highly advanced African nation of Wakanda as well as the powerful warrior known as the Black Panther.

name: BLACK WIDOW
biography: Despite super spy Natasha Romanoff’s checkered past, she’s become one of S.H.I.E.L.D.’s most deadly assassins and a frequent member of the Avengers.

name: BLADE
biography: A human-vampire hybrid since his tragic birth, Blade has spent his long life seeking to rid the world of vampires like the one that killed his mother. Over the years, he has mastered his own style of fighting monsters of all kinds.

name: BLINK
biography: Initially a timid, imprisoned mutant with the ability to warp time, Blink was given a second chance in a new reality to use her powers to fight massive enemies with the X-Men and Exiles.

name: CABLE
biography: Cable was sent to the future in a bid to save his life when he was infected by a techno-organic virus. Using his formidable telekinetic abilities and cybernetic enhancements, Cable battles Super Villain foes in his quest for peace.

name: CALAVERA
name2: CALAVERA (UNREVEALED IF THIS IS FIRST OR LAST NAME)

name: CALIBAN
biography: Caliban was once a weak, frightened mutant who lived underground. But once he began sensing other mutants around him, he surfaced and found other mutants who took him in.

name: CAPTAIN AMERICA
biography: Recipient of the Super-Soldier serum and World War II hero Steve Rogers fights for American ideals as one of the world’s mightiest heroes and the leader of the Avengers.

name: CAPTAIN AMERICA
name2: WILLIAM BURNSIDE (LEGALLY CHANGED IT TO "STEVEN ROGERS")

name: CAPTAIN UNIVERSE
name2: VARIABLE, IN THE PAST HAS INCLUDED: CAPTAIN RAY COFFIN, DOCTOR STRANGE/A>, PROFESSOR SWANN, COMMANDER ARCTURUS RANN, A MEMBER OF THE BADOON RACE,

name: CHASE STEIN
biography: Chase Stein grew up in an abusive household, so when he found out that his mother and father were members of a murderous cult called the Pride, he was happy to leave home and fight for good.

name: CLOAK
biography: Tyrone Johnson is able to access incredible powers that provide him with the ability to teleport and a connection with Tandy Bowen/Dagger.

name: COLLECTIVE MAN
name2: HAN, CHANG, LIN, SUN AND HO TAO-YU

name: THE COLLECTOR
biography: Taneleer Tivan is a primordial Elder of the Universe. At the inception of time, Tivan and his Elder compatriots rose to stand as some of the greatest powers in existence.

name: COLLEEN WING
biography: The trained samurai Colleen Wing uses her immense abilities as a master martial artist and swordswoman to protect the people of New York City.

name: CORVUS GLAIVE
biography: A loyal follower of Thanos, Corvus Glaive is a force to be reckoned with as he relentlessly strikes against those in his path.

name: COTTONMOUTH
biography: On the surface, Cornell Stokes is a criminal that runs the drug trade in New York City. But when someone crosses him, he becomes something far deadlier… At times a fearsome snakelike beast, this villain has some venom in his bite. He is Cottonmouth.

name: CRYSTAL
biography: Armed with the ability to command elements—and the restraint to use her power carefully—Crystal is one of the noblest members of the Inhuman Royal Family.

name: CUCKOO
name2: KAY CERA (POSSIBLY CHANGED FROM AN UNREVEALED NAME)

name: DAGGER
biography: Tandy found her perfect powered partner by accident, but her bond with Tyrone has made Cloak and Dagger a formidable pair. Dagger’s light forces are the ideal complement to Cloak’s darkness, and together they fight to keep New York City safe.

name: DAREDEVIL
biography: As a boy, Matt Murdock lost his sight—and gained superhuman senses—in an accident that taught him to live without fear. He went on to study law, leading him to a life of crime fighting in New York; as both a lawyer and as the vigilante Daredevil.

name: DEADPOOL
biography: Wade Wilson was born in Canada, but grew up to become the least Canadian person ever. When it comes to the Merc with a Mouth, with great power comes no responsibility.

name: DEVIL DINOSAUR
biography: The mutant Devil Dinosaur comes from a parallel universe where dinosaurs walk amongst early humans. Always a loyal companion, the red dino finds his way to the prime universe after the death of his first partner, and now fights with Luna Lafayette.

name: DIAMONDBACK
biography: Willis Stryker grew up alongside Carl Lucas, hustling to get by in a local gang. But as the pair grew up, Lucas chose a new path and became the Super Hero known as Luke Cage. Stryker, however, maintained his criminal course.

name: DOCTOR DOOM
biography: Victor Von Doom overcame his difficult childhood to become one of the world’s most brilliant scientists—though, at every turn, he saw his achievements outdone by a man called Reed Richards.

name: DOCTOR ERIK SELVIG
biography: Dr. Erik Selvig had no idea what he got himself into when he agreed to safeguard the fragments of the Cosmic Cube for S.H.I.E.L.D. Once he formed a bond with Kobik and had his memories replaced, he suddenly found his loyalties leaning toward evil.

name: DOCTOR STRANGE
biography: Formerly a renowned surgeon, Doctor Stephen Strange now serves as the Sorcerer Supreme—Earth’s foremost protector against magical and mystical threats.

name: DOMINO
biography: Domino survived a traumatic childhood to become one of the most dangerous mutant mercenaries in the Marvel Universe. Her ability to manipulate probability – ensuring her own good luck – can be a sneaky tool when she needs things to go her way.

name: DORMAMMU
biography: Originating in the aptly-named Dark Dimension, this incredibly powerful being has ominous plans for Earth and those who live there.

name: DRAX
biography: Drax is a brutish, battle-tested warrior. A former intergalactic criminal, Drax has no interest in money, only avenging his slain family. Reluctant at first, the hero with an unquenchable murderous rage joins the Guardians of the Galaxy.

name: EBONY MAW
biography: His allegiances may be unclear, but Ebony Maw’s ambitions are not to be doubted. As a henchman of Thanos, Maw can manipulate anyone to bend to his – or Thanos' – will. His powers have the ability to cause trouble for both sides of a battle.

name: EGO
biography: Ego, a powerful Celestial being and intergalactic explorer, traveled the cosmos in search of reuniting with his long-lost biological son, Peter Quill, and embarking on his most important mission together as father and son.

name: ELEKTRA
biography: An assassin and bounty hunter trained by the ancient ninja cult known as the Hand, Elektra Natchios has a history of getting her jobs done—even when her allies get in the way.

name: KILLMONGER
biography: Erik “Killmonger” Stevens challenged the Black Panther for the throne of Wakanda with special ops skills, devious tactics, and an eye on changing the world.

name: EXECUTIONER
biography: Asgardian warrior turned Executioner under Hela's command, Skurge deals with internal conflict as to whether he should save his people or exploit his newfound power.

name: FALCON
biography: Splitting time between his busy career as a Super Hero and his day job as a social worker, Harlem native Sam Wilson has made it his life’s work to carry on his late father’s message of hope and faith in humanity through his actions as Falcon.

name: FILIUS
name2: FILIUS (PRESUMABLY OMEN IS HIS LAST NAME)

name: FOGGY NELSON
biography: Behind every great attorney and vigilante is a devoted best friend like Franklin P. “Foggy” Nelson. It’s not easy living in Daredevil’s shadow, but Foggy Nelson, Esq. holds up pretty well, even if he does occasionally disagree over legal matters.

name: GAEA
name2: UNREVEALED; GAEA IS HER GREEK NAME

name: GAMORA
biography: Raised by Thanos to be a living weapon, Gamora seeks redemption as a member of the Guardians of the Galaxy, putting her extraordinary fighting abilities to good use.

name: GERTRUDE YORKES
biography: When Gertrude Yorkes found out that her parents were evil members of a homicidal cult called the Pride, she ran away, teaming up with the children of the rest of the cult members—and a psychically connected dinosaur named Old Lace.

name: GHOST RIDER
biography: Bonded with the demon Zarathos, the motorcycle stunt man Johnny Blaze becomes the feared Ghost Rider, who craves vengeances against the souls of those who would do the world harm in the world.

name: GHOST RIDER
biography: Despite being a talented car mechanic in his hometown of Los Angeles, Robbie Reyes never saw a bright future on the horizon. But when a he stole a muscle car and became possessed by his deceased evil uncle, Reyes became a Spirit of Vengeance.

name: GORGON
biography: Deriving his power from his muscular legs and beastly hooves, Gorgon is a wholly unique fighting force on behalf of his people and his homeland.

name: GRANDMASTER
biography: The Grandmaster is an ancient Elder of the universe that uses his all-encompassing power to force Super Heroes and Villains from across dimensions into his deadly cosmic games.

name: GREEN GOBLIN
biography: Norman Osborn is the father of Peter Parker’s best friend Harry – and Spider-Man’s long-time enemy. When Norman became the Green Goblin, he went on a maniacal rampage, forging a battle that continues to stalk Spidey.

name: GROOT
biography: This tree-like being branched out of his comfort zone to help the Guardians of the Galaxy keep the people of the universe safe.

name: GWENPOOL
biography: Gwenpool arrived in the Marvel Universe from the “real world,” but has wasted no time in making the most of her time in her fictional universe. Using her knowledge of comics to her advantage, Gwenpool causes and solves problems for her fellow heroes.

name: H.E.R.B.I.E.
name2: HUMANOID EXPERIMENTAL ROBOT B-TYPE INTEGRATED ELECTRONICS

name: HANK PYM
biography: Dr. Hank Pym creates the Pym Particle, which allows the user to alter their size or mass, greatly changing the landscape of super heroics with his invention. He uses his brilliance to fight first as Ant-Man, and then under many more monikers.

name: HAROLD MEACHUM
biography: Harold Meachum’s story is one of greed and fear. Once the business partner and friend of Wendell Rand, Meachum tried to wrest control of the shared company with murder.

name: HAWKEYE
biography: An expert marksman and fighter, Clint Barton puts his talents to good use by working for S.H.I.E.L.D. as a special agent. The archer known as Hawkeye also boasts a strong moral compass that at times leads him astray from his direct orders.

name: HAWKEYE
biography: Like Clint Barton with whom she shares a moniker, the strong-willed Kate Bishop is a masterful archer who uses her excellent marksmanship to fight against evil.

name: HEIMDALL
biography: An all-seeing Asgardian in charge of guarding the Rainbow Bridge known as Bifrost, Heimdall's keen skills serve him well as a first line of defense.

name: HELA
biography: Hela, Odin’s first born and sister to the Asgardian princes, seeks her place as the rightful heir of Asgard following the death of Odin and her release from imprisonment.

name: HELLCAT
biography: From a starstruck teen and wannabe hero to a faithful feline team member, Patsy Walker dreamt of being a Super Hero and got her wish! She just might not follow all the rules all the time.

name: HEPZIBAH
name2: A COMBINATION OF ODORS UNINTELLIGIBLE TO HUMANS

name: HORDE
name2: HORACIO CARRENAS, ELMIRA PHILLIPS, JOE FAMIGLIA, FLOYD HENDERSON, A DOG NAMED BACON, OTHER UNIDENTIFIED INDIVIDUALS

name: HOWARD STARK
biography: Howard Stark is a wealthy, extremely intelligent, and powerful industrialist. His most notable contribution, however, is that he raises his son to become one of Earth’s greatest heroes: Tony Stark, the Invincible Iron Man!

name: HULK
biography: Dr. Bruce Banner lives a life caught between the soft spoken scientist he’s always been and the uncontrollable green monster powered by his rage.

name: IMPOSSIBLE MAN
name2: POPPUPIANS HAVE NO NAMES; THEY KNOW WHO THEY ARE

name: INFERNO
biography: He is confident and handsome, but not great at taking orders or showing camaraderie. Dante's teammates will be the key to bringing friendship, heroism and light into his tortured soul.

name: IRON FIST
biography: Danny Rand’s life may have started in privilege, but it took a long journey into honor and strength. As the Iron Fist, Rand learned how to harness immense power, both mental and physical, to save others and fight honorable battles.

name: IRON MAN
biography: Inventor Tony Stark applies his genius for high-tech solutions to problems as Iron Man, the armored Avenger.

name: IRONHEART
biography: Genius Riri Williams, inspired by Tony Stark, decides to build her own suit of incredible armor to fight for the good of humanity. This super smart gal works hard and brings a lot of humanity to her role as the Super Hero Ironheart.

name: JEMMA SIMMONS
biography: Jemma Simmons is one of S.H.I.E.L.D.’s most exceptional scientists. Her brilliance in biology (both human and xeno) knows few parallels, and she is a cherished member of Phil Coulson’s special S.H.I.E.L.D. team.

name: JERYN HOGARTH
biography: As the right-hand man at Danny Rand’s day job, Jeryn Hogarth provides wise legal counsel for the Iron Fist and his allies. But sometimes his powerful connections get him mixed up in some serious trouble.

name: JESSICA JONES
biography: Overcoming her difficult past, Jessica Jones works as one of the finest Private Investigators in New York City. Her firm, Alias Investigations, was born out of her unmatched street smarts and her personal drive for justice.

name: BUSHMASTER
biography: Once nothing but an anonymous gang member, John McIver rose through the criminal ranks to become the heavyweight known as Bushmaster. Bushmaster’s influence across the underworld gives him the might to take on Heroes like Luke Cage and Iron Fist.

name: JONATHAN TREMONT
name2: UNREVEALED, LEGALLY CHANGED TO JONATHAN TREMONT

name: JOSIAH X
name2: JOSIAH AL HAJJ SADDIQ (LEGALLY CHANGED, FORMER LEGAL NAME UNREVEALED)

name: KAREN PAGE
biography: Karen Page has been a fixture at the offices of Nelson & Murdock from the very beginning. A loyal and competent secretary, Karen has been privy to many secrets, goings-on, and romantic advances from both Foggy Nelson and Matt Murdock, AKA Daredevil.

name: KARNAK
biography: One of the greatest hand-to-hand combatants the galaxy has ever seen, Karnak (with his enlarged cranium) is somewhat of an enigma within Inhuman society.

name: KAROLINA DEAN
biography: Karolina Dean once lived a pleasant life, with loving parents in a beautiful home. And then she discovered that not only were her mom and dad in a murderous cult, they were also aliens.

name: KINGPIN
biography: Wilson Fisk is power incarnate, he forces the criminal underworld of New York City to orbit around him. Having wrested control of the streets, Fisk became more than a crime boss; he is the Kingpin.

name: KLAW
biography: Mercenary and arms dealer Ulysses Klaue plied his trade in death to become the mortal enemy of the nation of Wakanda and its protector, the Black Panther.

name: LEAPER LOGAN
name2: LOGAN (UNREVEALED IF THIS IS HIS FIRST OR LAST NAME)

name: LEGION
biography: The mutant son of Charles Xavier, Haller’s mutant abilities pair with his dissociative identity disorder to give him the power of countless alternate personas, each with their own superhuman powers.

name: LEO FITZ
biography: Leo Fitz is a brilliant engineer whose gadgets and inventions are critical to S.H.I.E.L.D.’s success. This humorous and lighthearted agent also cares deeply about monkeys and works to acquire a simian assistant.

name: LOCKJAW
biography: Ever since he was a puppy, Lockjaw has been a faithful, fuzzy companion to the Inhuman royal family. Since being exposed to Terrigen mists, he gained the ability to teleport across time and space. He kindly requests that you play fetch with him.

name: LOKI
biography: God of Mischief and brother to Thor, Loki’s tricks and schemes wreak havoc across the realms.

name: LUKE CAGE
biography: After undergoing a variant of the Super-Soldier treatment in jail for a crime he didn't commit, the man formerly known as Carl Lucas was given superhuman strength and unbreakable skin. Adopting the name Power Man, Luke Cage became the Hero for Hire.

name: M
name2: MONET YVETTE CLARISSE MARIA THERESE ST. CROIX

name: MAGNETO
biography: Harnessing his powerful magnetic abilities, he has become a radical freedom fighter in the name of his kind. His only priority is the preservation of the mutant race—even at the expense of what some might deem to be the greater good.

name: MAGUS
biography: Created by the Enclave to be part of a race of super humans who would abolish war, illness, and crime, Adam Warlock is a unique being who uses his immense and formidable powers to safeguard the universe.

name: MALCOLM POWDER
biography: Though she’ll never admit it, teenager Malcolm Powder proves to be a useful ally and colleague to Jessica Jones in her private investigation career. As a huge fan of hers, he strives to support her in any way he can.

name: NAKIA
biography: The Wakandan Nakia protects her country from outside forces as a War Dog, one of its most accomplished espionage agents.

name: MANTIS
biography: Mantis uses her powers to protect the galaxy against those who would seek to harm it.

name: MARIA HILL
biography: Ruthless, determined, and efficient, Maria Hill makes an excellent second-in-command to Nick Fury and, later, director of S.H.I.E.L.D.

name: MAXIMUS
biography: Mad but brilliant, Maximus has spent his life trying to take the Inhumans’ throne from his brother Black Bolt. Despite his intelligence, his grudge and insanity have only caused the oft-imprisoned Inhuman pain and frustration.

name: MEDUSA
biography: She may not have volunteered for the job, but Medusa has spent most of her life as the queen of the Inhumans, standing up for the rights of her race against enemies in her own family and beyond.

name: MELINDA MAY
biography: As one of S.H.I.E.L.D.'s deadliest fighters, Agent May lives up to her nickname—"The Cavalry."

name: MERCURIO
name2: MERCURIO (NAME IN HIS OWN LANGUAGE IS UNKNOWN)

name: MICRO
biography: David Lieberman is one of the finest hackers in the world. And as the Punisher’s ally and accomplice, Lieberman uses his high tech skills to deadly effect. A vital asset to one of the deadliest men in existence, he is known as Microchip.

name: MISS AMERICA
biography: She has a strong independent streak, which makes her less quick to gel into the team dynamic with the others. She openly rejects leadership, preferring to do her own thing and act in her own best interest.

name: MISTY KNIGHT
biography: When an explosion left her without an arm, police officer Misty Knight didn’t give up her desire to help others. With her bionic arm, she continues to defend and protect the innocent of New York City.

name: MOLLY HAYES
biography: The young mutant Molly Hayes runs away with her friends when they all discover that their parents are Super Villains. Proud of her super strength, Molly uses her powers with joy to defend her fellow Runaways and fight all kinds of opponents.

name: MOON GIRL
biography: Lunella Lafayette, nine-year-old genius, also has giant red Dinosaur who she can switch brains with as her close friend and ally. She uses all her vast abilities and talents to protect the world as the Super Hero, Moon Girl.

name: MR. FROST
name2: UNREVEALED (FROST COULD POTENTIALLY BE HIS LAST NAME)

name: MS. MARVEL
biography: She's got a big heart and isn't as quick to judge others as some of her teammates, allowing her to find the truth about Inferno. Kamala is getting pretty good at using her new powers and is determined to prove that she can be a great hero.

name: NAMOR THE SUB-MARINER
biography: The offspring of an Atlantean princess and an American explorer, the powerful mutant Namor is a force to behold. While he occasionally leaves his kingdom to work with - or fight against - humanity, Atlantis is always his utmost priority.

name: NAMORITA
name2: NAMORITA (LEGALLY NAMORITA "NITA" PRENTISS IN SURFACE SOCIETY)

name: NEBULA
biography: As a pirate and mercenary with her intentions set on conquering other empires, this daughter of Thanos is feared by many across the star systems.

name: NICO MINORU
biography: Nico Minoru is a regular teenage girl until she absorbs the powerful and magical Staff of One, during an attack by her own mother. Banding together with her friends to form the Runaways, Nico defies her villainous parentage.

name: NIGHT NURSE
biography: Linda Carter takes on the moniker of Night Nurse in order to help and heal Super Heroes who are in need.

name: NIGHTSHADE
biography: Spurred by a lust for power and a brilliant scientific mind, Tilda Johnson invented serums that create werewolves, brainwash allies, and disarm Super Heroes, she has succeeded in making a name for herself in the world of criminal activity.

name: NUKE
biography: A Vietnam War veteran, Frank Simpson had his past battlefield trauma weaponized when he was brainwashed into becoming a savage, mindless killing machine. Simpson received an appropriate nickname given his destructive and deadly presence: Nuke.

name: ODIN
biography: King of Asgard and protector of the Nine Realms, Odin the All-Father once lead with only conquest in mind. Eventually, he recognized the benefits of lasting peace and changed his ways.

name: OKOYE
biography: Okoye serves the Black Panther as a personal bodyguard and the nation of Wakanda as a torchbearer of tradition and virtue. Okoye is as deadly as she is wise, and stands as one of T’Challa’s most trusted allies and companions.

name: ORIGIN
name2: UNREVEALED (SAID TO BE UNPRONOUNCEABLE BY HUMANS)

name: PATRIOT
biography: Rayshaun is a natural-born leader and quick to leap into action to impress his S.H.I.E.L.D. seniors. He strives to live up to Captain America's conflict with Doreen. He values integrity, honesty, and order above all.

name: PEGGY CARTER
biography: Peggy Carter began her career fighting alongside French Resistance during World War II. Following her stint in Europe, she teamed up with Captain America as an Avengers auxiliary before becoming one of S.H.I.E.L.D.'s most decorated agents.

name: POLARIS
biography: The green-haired Polaris is a powerful mutant, like her father before her, and has a complicated history with the rest of the mutant community. Her powers allow her to control magnetic fields, making her a true force to be reckoned with.

name: PROXIMA MIDNIGHT
biography: As one of the most fierce and formidable warriors in the cosmos, Proxima Midnight mercilessly uses her lethal skills to serve her adopted father Thanos in his quest to obtain all six Infinity Stones and erase half of all life in the universe.

name: PUNISHER
biography: Frank Castle used to be a good man. Frank Castle used to be a family man. But now Frank Castle has nothing. Now Frank Castle is the Punisher.

name: Não encontrado (1799)
biography: Zebediah Killgrave does not attack his enemies with brute force, or advanced weaponry, or alien allies. He simply uses his mind and the mind of his foe—or victim.

name: QUAKE
biography: Daisy puts more pressure on herself than she should. Though rising in the S.H.I.E.L.D. ranks, she's not afraid to break a few rules to protect her friends or those in need.

name: ROCKET
biography: As the weapons and tactical expert of the Guardians of the Galaxy, Rocket risks his hide to defend the cosmos.

name: ROGUE
biography: After she discovered her mutant powers—that, by touch, she was able to absorb memories, powers, and personality traits from others—Rogue went on a long journey that ultimately led her to become a leader for both the X-Men and the Avengers.

name: SCARLET WITCH
biography: Notably powerful, Wanda Maximoff has fought both against and with the Avengers, attempting to hone her abilities and do what she believes is right to help the world.

name: SCORPION
name2: THASANEE RAPPUCCINI; LEGALLY CHANGED TO CARMILLA BLACK

name: SHADES
biography: Growing up on the streets, Shades had to muscle his own way into power. Shades took to the criminal lifestyle for good, forging his own dangerous path alongside his longtime friend and partner-in-crime, Comanche.

name: SHADOW KING
biography: One of the only mutants whose psionic abilities can rival those of Professor Charles Xavier, the man known as the Shadow King lets no one stand between him and his efforts to control the astral plane.

name: SHE-HULK
biography: After getting a blood transfusion from her cousin Bruce Banner, Jennifer Walters gained all the powers of the Hulk – and all the problems. But while she gained massive strength, she never lost her passion for justice.

name: SHOCKER
biography: Herman Schultz, known as the Shocker, builds himself a pair of signature vibro-shock gloves to help him succeed with his criminal schemes.

name: SHURI
biography: As part of the Wakandan royal line, she has developed her own physical strength and vast knowledge. But once she became the Black Panther herself, she was nearly unstoppable - a hero in her own right.

name: SIF
biography: An Asgardian goddess and everlasting comrade to Thor, Sif has long served as a warrior across the realms on behalf of her friends and her homeland.

name: SKINNER
name2: UNREVEALED (POSSIBLY SKINNER OR JOHN, LAST NAME UNREVEALED)

name: SPIDER-MAN
biography: In the alternate reality of Earth-1610, a young New York City teen was bitten by a genetically enhanced spider. When the Peter Parker of that dimension was killed, the teen—named Miles Morales—was inspired to take up the fallen mantle.

name: SPIDER-MAN
biography: Bitten by a radioactive spider, Peter Parker’s arachnid abilities give him amazing powers he uses to help others, even while his personal life continues to offer plenty of obstacles.

name: GHOST-SPIDER
biography: Gwen was bitten by a radioactive spider and gained spider-like powers. Influenced by her father's moral code, Gwen uses her powers to help those in need like her friend, Peter Parker.

name: SPIDER-WOMAN
biography: Jessica Drew was placed into a hibernation chamber for years before emerging decades later still a teenager. Physically enhanced by a special spider-derived serum, Drew chose to take her life into her own hands and became known as Spider-Woman.

name: SQUIRREL GIRL
biography: Because Doreen comes across as silly, many of her teammates enjoy her company but don't take her too seriously, except for Kamala, her new best friend. Doreen yearns for all of them to respect her more, but she won't give up the positivity.

name: STAR-LORD
biography: Leader of the Guardians of the Galaxy, Peter Quill, known as Star-Lord, brings a sassy sense of humor while protecting the universe from any and all threats.

name: STEEL SERPENT
biography: A long-time nemesis of the Iron Fist, Davos nearly claimed the prestigious title for himself – but wasn’t deemed worthy. His rage and jealousy have fueled his hatred for Danny Rand.

name: STEPFORD CUCKOOS
name2: CELESTE, ESME (DECEASED), IRMA (AKA "MINDEE"), PHOEBE, SOPHIE (DECEASED) (SURNAME UNREVEALED)

name: STICK
biography: While he’s mainly known as the man who trained Daredevil, Stick is a character who has his own rich history of fighting evil. After all, Matt Murdock wouldn’t have become the hero that he did if not for the discipline taught to him by Stick.

name: STORM
biography: As a storied, veteran X-Men member, Ororo Munroe - aka Storm - is one of the most powerful mutants on Earth. A trusted and wise leader of the team, with the ability to control and manipulate weather patterns, Storm has created a legacy.

name: SUPERGIANT
biography: The telepathic Supergiant is an integral member of Thanos’ Black Order, a group dedicated to helping the Titan achieve his conquest goals. She uses her ability of mental manipulation to faithfully serve her master and break down resistance in his way

name: THANOS
biography: The Mad Titan Thanos quests across the universe in search of the Infinity Stones, intending to use their limitless power for shocking purposes.

name: THENA
name2: THENA (CHANGED BY ROYAL DECREE FROM HER ORIGINAL NAME, AZURA)

name: THOR
biography: The son of Odin uses his mighty abilities as the God of Thunder to protect his home Asgard and planet Earth alike.

name: THUNDERBIRD
biography: The brave mutant John Proudstar fought alongside the X-Men, seeking to honor his Native American ancestry. Unfortunately, he didn’t stay on the team for long, as his rash personality led to an untimely demise.

name: TRITON
biography: A member of the Inhuman Royal Family, Triton was exposed to the transformative powers of the Terrigen Mists at an unusually young age. Triton quickly mastered his skills as an aquatic fighting force.

name: ULTRON
biography: The creation gone awry, the sentient robot Ultron hates and seeks to wipe out humanity.

name: UNUM
name2: UNUM (THE ACTUAL NAMES OF THE BEINGS THAT HAVE BEEN MERGED INTO HER CONSCIOUSNESS ARE UNREVEALED)

name: UNUS
name2: ANGELO UNUSCIONE, LEGALLY CHANGED TO GUNTHER BAIN

name: VALKYRIE
biography: Gifted the power of the legendary Asgardian Brunnhilde, Parrington assumed the mantle and the cosmic responsibilities of the Valkyrie.

name: VENOM
biography: When Spider-Man acquired a living symbiote costume, he had no idea that it would later spawn a major adversary. Though it often acts as a foe to the Wallcrawler, Venom does possess some kind of morality—avoiding harm to the innocent and bringing down

name: THE VISION
biography: The android called Vision defies physics and fights as an Avenger with the power of density manipulation and his flawless computer brain.

name: VULTURE
biography: Adrian Toomes aka the Vulture is one of Peter Parker’s most enduring enemies. With a grudge against Spider-Man and a genius-caliber talent for invention, the Vulture can soar across the skies in contraptions of his very own.

name: WAR MACHINE
biography: Air Force Lieutenant Colonel James “Rhodey” Rhodes exudes loyalty and courage, whether flying a plane or piloting the War Machine armor.

name: WARD MEACHUM
biography: Ward Meachum has a taste for revenge – but not as much as he has a taste for power and profits. His grudge against Danny Rand started before his brother Harold was murdered, and he continued his pursuit for the top with some nefarious characters.

name: WARLOCK
name2: WARLOCK (ENGLISH APPROXIMATION OF HIS NAME IN HIS NATIVE LANGUAGE)

name: WASP
biography: Janet van Dyne flies high and stings hard as the Wasp, the size-changing founding Avenger with an impeccable fashion sense.

name: WASP
biography: While the lost daughter of Hank Pym inherits his scientific mind, Nadia Pym follows in the footsteps of her step-mother Janet van Dyne to carve out a place for herself in the Super Hero community as the Unstoppable Wasp.

name: WEREWOLF BY NIGHT
name2: JACOB RUSSOFF (GIVEN NAME), JACK RUSSELL (ADOPTED NAME)

name: WICCAN
biography: As a Young Avenger, Wiccan puts his powerful magical abilities to help protect and serve humanity. The young sorcerer also explores his heritage, as he is the reincarnation of one of Scarlet Witch and Vision’s twins.

name: WINTER SOLDIER
biography: James Buchanan “Bucky” Barnes enlists to fight in World War II, but eventually literally falls in battle. Unfortunately, the evil Arnim Zola recovers him and erases his memory, turning him into a highly-trained assassin called the Winter Soldier.

name: WOLVERINE
biography: From the northern wilderness of Canada hails one of the gruffest, most irascible, totally cynical and brooding member of the X-Men ever to grace the team with his presence.

name: WONG
biography: A master of the martial and mystic arts, Wong is a close companion of Doctor Strange.

name: YO-YO
biography: As a member of the Secret Warriors, Yo-Yo Rodriguez uses her super speed powers to help S.H.I.E.L.D. protect the innocent. Though she had her arms severed during a mission, Yo-Yo continues to fight on with cybernetic arms and a rebellious spirit.

name: YONDU
biography: Space pirate Yondu Udonta leads his group of Ravagers across the galaxy, always looking for his next big score.

name: ZERO
name2: A.D.A.M. UNIT (AMBIENT-ENERGY DAMPENING ACTUALIZATION MODULE) UNIT ZERO
